To create a Chrome Extension that allows users to watch a video at the same time using JW Player, you can follow these steps:

1. Create a new folder for your extension and initialize a new npm project:

```
mkdir my-extension
cd my-extension
npm init -y
```

2. Create a `manifest.json` file in the root directory with the following content:

```json
{
  "manifest_version": 2,
  "name": "JW Player Watch Party",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "Create a shared watch party using JW Player",
  "permissions": [
    "activeTab",
    "storage",
    "http://*/*",
    "https://*/*"
  ],
  "background": {
    "scripts": ["background.js"],
    "persistent": false
  },
  "content_scripts": [
    {
      "matches": ["https://*/*"],
      "js": ["content.js"]
    }
  ],
  "browser_action": {
    "default_popup": "popup.html",
    "default_icon": {
      "16": "images/icon16.png",
      "48": "images/icon48.png",
      "128": "images/icon128.png"
    }
  },
